definition.value: An amino tetrasaccharide comprised of a linear sequence of N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine, alpha-D-galactose, beta-D-galactose and beta-D-glucose residues linked (1->3), (1->6) and (1->4).
An alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-D-Galp in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.
A C16 polyunsaturated fatty acid that is the (10R,11S)-epoxy derivative of trideca-2,6-dienoic acid.
